# EcoPoints Admin Dashboard Updates

## Overview
Comprehensive updates to the admin dashboard based on `New Updates.txt` requirements. The updates span across multiple areas including login/signup flow, navigation, dashboard components, user management, rewards, system logs, and general UI/UX improvements.

---

## Phase 1: Login/Signup Modal Enhancements
- [ ] 1.1 Shorten transition animation timing between login and signup modes
- [ ] 1.2 Display EcoPoints logo on colored card during animation transition
- [ ] 1.3 Add new signup fields:
  - [ ] Role dropdown (Student, Faculty, Admin, Staff)
  - [ ] Searchable school dropdown with Google Maps API integration

---

## Phase 2: Side Navigation Bar Updates
- [ ] 2.1 Change sign-out button hover color from green to red
- [ ] 2.2 Implement dropdown close behavior (User Management/System Logs collapse when Dashboard/Locations active)

---

## Phase 3: Dashboard Overview Updates
- [ ] 3.1 Remove decorative elements from stat cards (except Machines card photo)
- [ ] 3.2 Fix Recycling Trends chart logic:
  - Day view: Sunday to Saturday
  - Weekly view: Week 1-4 (month-aware, leap year aware)
  - Monthly view: January to December
- [ ] 3.3 Quick Actions updates:
  - Replace Settings with Rewards (with link)
  - Rename "View Logs" to "Admin Logs"
  - Link "Admin Logs" to Admin Access page (not Bottle Logs)
  - Implement role-based shortcuts (e.g., Inventory Officer sees Rewards Management)

---

## Phase 4: Data Logs Overview (Dashboard)
- [ ] 4.1 Rename title from "Real-Time Data Logs" to "Real-Time Bottle Logs"
- [ ] 4.2 Add Location column (school deployed)
- [ ] 4.3 Remove Log ID column, add User ID column
- [ ] 4.4 Add Condition column with bottle points system:
  - Small PET (290-350ml): 5 pts with label/cap, 3 pts without
  - Medium PET (350-500ml): 8 pts with label/cap, 5 pts without
  - Large PET (750-1000ml): 10 pts with label/cap, 7 pts without
  - Invalid Size (>1000ml): 0 pts - Rejected

---

## Phase 5: Machine Management Updates
- [ ] 5.1 Remove fill level display from machine cards
- [ ] 5.2 Change Maintenance button color to blue (instead of orange)
- [ ] 5.3 Log all machine actions to Machine Logs
- [ ] 5.4 Restrict access to Head Admin and Technician roles only

---

## Phase 6: User Management - All Users Section
- [ ] 6.1 Update pagination summary to "Showing 1 to 10 of 14 users" format
- [ ] 6.2 Separate Username and User ID into distinct columns
- [ ] 6.3 Enhance search function (User ID, Username, Email) with placeholder hint
- [ ] 6.4 Add filters:
  - School dropdown (Super Admin only, dynamic based on system locations)
  - Area dropdown (Local Admins only)
  - Toggle: Alphabetical Username (A-Z)
  - Toggle: Points (High to Low / Low to High)
- [ ] 6.5 Add border and hover effect to Clear Filter button (apply to all tables)
- [ ] 6.6 Move Add User feature to Manage Admins section
- [ ] 6.7 Create new Add User button with same fields as updated signup form

---

## Phase 7: User Management - Permissions/Manage Admins Section
- [ ] 7.1 Rename "Permissions" to "Manage Admins"
- [ ] 7.2 Filter to show only admin panel users (not machine users)
- [ ] 7.3 Add new Technician role (access: Machines menu + Machine Logs only)
- [ ] 7.4 Remove machine permission from Inventory Officer role
- [ ] 7.5 Remove machine permission from Auditor role
- [ ] 7.6 Move Add Users feature here, rename to "Add Admin"
- [ ] 7.7 Disable delete action on System Logs (show "-" instead)

